.TH "funzyto770" "1" "2026-06-09" "" "funzyto770 User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
funzyto770 - Thomson TO7 and TO7-70 home computer emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R] [\f[B]-k\f[R] \f[I]keyfile\f[R]] [\f[B]-gray\f[R]]
[\f[B]-mono\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]funzyto770\f[R] emulates the Thomson TO7 and TO7-70, French 8-bit
home computers based on the Motorola 6809E processor.
The emulator requires an X11 display and emulates the following
hardware:
.IP \[bu] 2
Motorola 6809E CPU
.IP \[bu] 2
optical pen (light pen)
.IP \[bu] 2
joysticks (2)
.IP \[bu] 2
cassette tape reader (.k7 format)
.IP \[bu] 2
removable memo7 ROM cartridges (16 KB each)
.PP
On startup, the emulator loads the TO7 high ROM from the file
\f[B]romto770\f[R] and the BASIC cartridge from \f[B]memo7/basic\f[R],
both expected in the current working directory.
It then drops into the interactive monitor.
.SS Monitor
.PP
The monitor is a text-mode interface that controls the emulator.
The following commands are available:
.TP
\f[B]go\f[R]
Start or resume emulation.
.TP
\f[B]reset\f[R]
Simulate pressing the TO7 reset button.
.TP
\f[B]k7\f[R] \f[I]filename\f[R]
Load a new cassette tape file (.k7 format).
.TP
\f[B]seek\f[R] \f[I]hex\f[R]
Set the cassette tape position (hexadecimal value).
.TP
\f[B]load\f[R] \f[I]filename\f[R]
Load a memo7 ROM cartridge image.
.TP
\f[B]speed\f[R] \f[I]hex\f[R]
Adjust the emulation slow-down loop counter.
Use 0 for full speed.
.TP
\f[B]dir\f[R]
List files in the current directory.
.TP
\f[B]cd\f[R] \f[I]directory\f[R]
Change the current directory.
.TP
\f[B]pwd\f[R]
Print the current directory.
.TP
\f[B]q\f[R]
Quit the emulator.
.SS Mouse controls during emulation
.TP
\f[B]Right button\f[R]
Suspend emulation and return to the monitor.
.TP
\f[B]Middle button\f[R]
Move the light pen across the screen (held down while moving).
.TP
\f[B]Left button\f[R]
Press the light pen tip (trigger).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-k\f[R] \f[I]keyfile\f[R]
Keyboard layout file to use.
Defaults to \f[B]keyto7\f[R] in the current directory.
This file is generated by \f[B]funzy_enterkey\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[B]-gray\f[R]
Use a greyscale palette (for greyscale displays).
.TP
\f[B]-mono\f[R]
Use strictly monochrome rendering (for monochrome displays).
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]keyto7\f[R]
Default keyboard layout file, generated by \f[B]funzy_enterkey\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[I]romto770\f[R]
TO7 high ROM image (6144 bytes).
Required.
Place in the working directory.
Obtain with \f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[I]memo7/basic\f[R]
BASIC cartridge image (16384 bytes).
Loaded automatically on startup.
Obtain with \f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R](1).
.TP
\f[I]memo7/\f[R]
Directory holding additional memo7 cartridge images.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run the emulator with the default keyboard layout:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzyto770
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Run the emulator with a custom keyboard layout:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzyto770 -k mykeymap
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Once in the monitor, start emulation:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
ok
0000 > go
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Load a program from cassette and run it:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
ok
0000 > k7 myprog.k7
ok
0000 > go
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]funzy_enterkey\f[R](1), \f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R](1),
\f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R](1), \f[B]funzy_wav2k7\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
